अक्ष
अक्ष m. (v. ईक्ष् videre)<BR>1) oculus, in fine compositorum<BR>pro अक्षि — v. gr. 681. — e. c. पिङ्गाक्ष q. v. (gr.<BR>ὌΣΣΟ, ὌΚΚΟ per assimilationem ex ὌΞΟ, lat. oculus<BR>abjecto s, goth. augô — Th. augan — contra legem<BR>quâ plerumque tenues in aspiratas sunt conversae, quam<BR>ob rem auhô exspectaveris, cujus au ex vi euphonica litterae<BR>h explicari posset, ita ut genuinum a in u sit attenuatum<BR>(*) — sicut e. c. in lith. ugni-s = अग्नि ignis — vocali<BR>u vero, propter sequens h, a euphonicum sit<BR>praefixum; russ. òko; v. अक्षि).<BR>2) talus. N. 7.5.<BR>3) rota<BR>(cf. lat. axis = अक्षि q. v.; gr. ἈΞΟΝ = अक्षन् q. v.;<BR>germ. vet. ahsa, nostrum Achse; lith. aʃzis ejecto क्, ʃz<BR>= ष्).<BR>4) currus.<BR>5) secundum Wils. a kind of seed<BR>used for rosaries (Eloeocarpus).<BR>6) dica, lis.<BR>(*) V. librum meum „Vocalismus” p. 227. n. 16.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=001-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=31" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षदर्शक
अक्षदर्शक m. (TATP. e praec. sgnf. 6. et दर्शक qui videt)<BR>judex. AM.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=002-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=32" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अक्षन्
अक्षन् Thema defectivum, quo suppletur अक्षि oculus (gr. 165.<BR>cf. goth. Th. AUGAN, unde nomin. augô).<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=002-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=33" target="_blank">Correction</a>

