अञ्च्
1. अञ्च् 1. P. A. (grammatici scribunt etiam अच्, gr. 110^a).)<BR>1) ire, in compositis ut प्राच्, quod in casibus fortibus<BR>sonat प्राञ्च्, v. gr. 196. sq.<BR>2) venerari, colere. — अञ्चित<BR>1) erectus, de pilis, v. apud Wils. रोमाञ्चित<BR>«having the hair of the body erect, considered as a proof of<BR>exquisite pleasure, enraptured, delighted».<BR>2) pulcher, de<BR>oculis, palpebris et superciliis, ubi primitive item «erectus»<BR>significare videtur: N. 12.45. अञ्चितेक्षण pulchros<BR>oculos habens; RAGH. 5.76. अञ्चिताक्षिपक्ष्मन्<BR>pulchras oculorum palpebras habens (Comment. Calc.<BR>{#aYcitAni sundarARi akznor netrayor pakzmARi<BR>yasya#}); अञ्चितभ्रू f. Wils. ed. 2. «a woman having beautifull<BR>eye brows».<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=004-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=107" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्च्
2. अञ्च् 10. P. (व्यक्तायाम् वाचि K. व्यक्तौ V.) clare, distincte<BR>loqui.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=004-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=108" target="_blank">Correction</a>

