अञ्ज्
अञ्ज् 7. 10. P. (अनज्मि, अञ्जयामि; अञ्ज् 10. a grammaticis<BR>scribitur अज्)<BR>1) ire, v. अञ्जस्.<BR>2) splendere.<BR>3) oblinere, ungere, praesertim cl. 10. MAN. 4.44.: {#aYjayantI<BR>svake netre#} oblinens oculos suos (lat. ungo).<BR>c. वि Caus.<BR>1) manifestare, arguere. MAN. 10.38. Pass.<BR>व्यज्यते (gr. 503. 538.). HIT. 103.20.<BR>2) creare. MAN. 1.6.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=005-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=113" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्जन
अञ्जन n. collyrium. HIT. 74.4.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=005-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=114" target="_blank">Correction</a>

अञ्जलि
अञ्जलि m. manuum junctio, implicatio (Wils. explicat:<BR>The cavity formed by putting the hands together and hollowing<BR>the palms, as if to receive water, etc.).<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=005-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=115" target="_blank">Correction</a>

