इट्
इट् 1. P. (गत्याम्) ire (ortum esse videtur ex trita radice<BR>अट्, attenuato अ in इ, quâ in re formae इट् et अट्<BR>eandem rationem inter se tenent quam goth. Praesentia<BR>veluti lisa lego eorumque Praeterita sing. quae primitivum<BR>a servarunt, sicut las, v. gr. comp. 109^a).<BR>1) p. 116.).<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=038-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=1112" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इट्चर
इट्चर m. (ad voluntatem iens ex इष् desiderans - v.<BR>gr. 74. - et चर iens) taurus libertate gaudens. AM.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=038-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=1113" target="_blank">Correction</a>

इडा
