ऋति
ऋति f. (r. ऋ s. ति)<BR>1) itio.<BR>2) via.<BR>3) felicitas. (Hib.<BR>raith «prosperity, encrease, profit, benefit, good»; raite<BR>«ways, passages, roads»; fortasse lat. rîte a th. rîti, nostrum<BR>Art, v. Graff. I.403.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=056-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=1606" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋतीया
ऋतीया f. (r. ऋत् s. ईया) vituperatio, reprehensio. AM.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=056-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=1607" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ऋतु
ऋतु m. (r. ऋ s. तु)<BR>1) anni tempus. BH. 10.35. (*)<BR>2) mensis.<BR>3) menstrua (Ita अमस् tempus a r. अम् ire; c. ऋतु<BR>cf. hib. raithe «a quarter of a year»; huc etiam traxerim<BR>hib. alt - ex primitivâ formâ अर्तु mutato r in l<BR>1)<BR>«time».<BR>2) «a joint, an article»; lat. ar-tus et ri-tus,<BR>ita ut utrumque a movendo sit nominatum).<BR>(*) Wils. ad hanc vocem: The Hindu year is divided into<BR>six seasons, each consisting of two months. AM.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=056-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=1608" target="_blank">Correction</a>

