गुर् 1. et 6. P. गोरामि, गुरामि (उद्यमे) tollere, sublevare;<BR>cf. गुर्व्, ग्रह्.<BR>c. अव 6. P. invadere, impetum facere in alqm., c. loc.<BR>MAN. 4.169.: {#na kadAcid dvije tasmAd vidvAn avagured<BR>api#}; 11.206. 208.: अवगूर्य, v. gr. 635. 5. (Schol.<BR>अवगुर् per दण्डाद्युद्यमने explicat.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=106-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2857" target="_blank">Correction</a>

गुरु
गुरु<BR>1) Adj. (f. गुर्वी) gravis, transl. eximius, venerandus.<BR>BH. 6.22. A. 5.7. BR. 2.6. IN. 5.41.<BR>2) Subst. magister<BR>et quaevis utriusque sexûs persona propinquae cognationis<BR>causâ imprimis veneranda. BH. 2.5. IN. 4.9. 5.19. 41.<BR>SU. 4.15. - Dual. गुरू parentes. SA. 4.22. (गुरु ortum<BR>est e गरु mutato अ in उ, ut videtur, pervim assimilationis<BR>litterae finalis, sicut supra गिरि e गरि; ab obsoleto<BR>गरु venit compar. गरीयस्, superl. गरिष्ठ et gr.<BR>βαϱύς, mutatâ gutturali in labialem, sicut in βίβημι et<BR>βοῦς, v. गा, गो; lat. gravis per metathesin ortum est e<BR>garvis, e garuis, adjecto i, sicut in aliis, qui primitive in u<BR>desinunt, adjectivis; e. c. tenuis = तनु, τανυ; goth.<BR>kauriths gravatus; lith. giéras bonus.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=106-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2858" target="_blank">Correction</a>

