ग्रह्
ग्रह् 1. 10. P. praesertim 9. P. A. {#grahAmi, grahayAmi, gfhRAmi,<BR>gfhRe#}. (Haec radix in iis, quae Gunam non assumunt,<BR>formis, syllabam र in ऋ corripit et vocalem intermediam<BR>इ in ई producit, unde part. in त गृहीत,<BR>gerundd. गृहीत्वा, गृह्य, praet. mltf. अग्रहिषम्; Pass.<BR>गृह्ये; Desid. जिघृक्ष् (*), gr. 102.d.)<BR>1) capere, sumere,<BR>accipere, prehendere, tollere. BHAG. 2.22.: {#vAsAMsi<BR>navAni gfhRAti#}; IN. 1.27.: {#pItvA pARIyam tezAm<BR>arTena jagrAha#}; RAGH. 1.18.: बलिम् अग्रहीत्; MAN. 5.157.:<BR>न नामा ऽपि गृह्णीयात् परस्य; RAGH. 5.59.: {#astramantraN<BR>jagrAha tasmAt#}; IN. 2.20.: {#pARO gfhItvE<BR>'nam#}; N. 1.19.: तेषाम् एकञ् जग्राह पक्षिणम्; 20.: {#pawe<BR>nipatite tadA grahIzyAmI#} (**) {#'ti taM rAjA nalam<BR>Aha#}.<BR>2) captare. N. 1.24.: {#grahItuN KagamAMs tvaramARo<BR>'pacakrame#}.<BR>3) percipere, audire. RAGH. 11.15.: {#jyAninAdam<BR>aTa gfhRatI tayoH#}. — Caus. facere ut aliquis<BR>capiat etc. RAGH. 15.88.: {#AtodyaN grAhayAmAsa samatyAjayad<BR>AyuDam#}; HIT. 7.21.: {#nItividyAN grAhayituM<BR>Sakyante#}. (Primitiva huius radicis forma est ग्रभ्,<BR>unde ग्रह्, relictâ solâ aspiratione litterae भ्; v. gr. comp. 23.;<BR>forma ग्रभ् servata est in dialecto vêd., quae item<BR>syllabam र, ubi grammaticae leges Gunam non postulant,<BR>in ऋ corripit; in lingua zend. haec radix sonat 𐬔𐬆𐬭𐬆𐬞<BR>gĕrĕp ante t, et 𐬔𐬇𐬎𐬭𐬎𐬎 geurv ante vocales, v. gram.<BR>comp. 109^b).2. Cf. goth. greipa, nostrum greife, lith.<BR>grếbju prehendo, pagrếbju abripio, slav. grabljû rapio,<BR>cum l euphonico; hib. grabaim «I devour; I stop, interrupt,<BR>disturb»; v. विग्रह् pugnare; gabhaim «I take, receive,<BR>conceive» ejecto r; fortasse eodem modo nostrum<BR>gebe, a rad. gab, goth. giba, gaf, gêbum, huc pertinet, [Page111-a+ 37]<BR>ita quidem ut sensu respondeat formae caus. ग्रभयामि.<BR>Etiam nostrum Gabel, germ. vet. gabala furca<BR>tanquam instrumentum sumendo inserviens huc traxerim<BR>(cf. gr. ϰϱεάγϱα). E graecâ linguâ huc retulerim γϱῖϕος, γϱῖπος,<BR>rete, ita ut a capiendo sint nominata.<BR>Fortasse ἀγϱεύω, ἀγϱέω dissolvenda sunt in ἀ-γϱεύω, ἀ-γϱέω,<BR>abjectâ radicis consonante finali, ita ut ἀ respondeat<BR>praepositioni आ vel अव. Lat. prehendo e<BR>grehendo ortum esse possit, mutatâ gutturali in labialem<BR>et mediâ in tenuem, sicut in gr. ϰλέπτω. Adjectum end<BR>referri potest ad âna Imperativi गृहाण, vel, quod ad<BR>idem redit, ad ना τοῦ गृह्णामि etc., adjecto d post n, sicut<BR>e. c. in tendo = तन् et nostro Hund = श्वन्, शुनस्,<BR>ϰύων, ϰυνός. Fortasse gra-tus sicut nostrum angenehm<BR>et idem valens acceptus ab accipiendo est dictum,<BR>abjectâ consonante finali; v. etiam ग्रह् praef. अनु. Lat.<BR>rapio et gr. ἁϱπάζω e grapio, γϱαπάζω mutilata esse<BR>possent, sicut nascor e gnascor, nosco e gnosco, νοῦς e<BR>γνοῦς; respiciatur etiam scr. लभ्, quod fortasse ante<BR>linguarum separationem e ग्रभ् vel ग्लभ् mutilatum est,<BR>quum antiquitas formae लभ् cognato graeco ΛΑΒ et<BR>hib. lamh manus confirmetur.<BR>c. अनु<BR>1) favere, fortunare, beare, adjuvare, c. acc. pers.<BR>et instr. rei. HIT. 17.6.: माम् मैत्र्येणा ऽनुगृहीतुम् अर्हसि;<BR>33.12.: अनेन मित्रेणा ऽहं स्नेहानुवृत्त्या ऽनुगृहीतः;<BR>RAGH. 8.85.: कुटुम्बिनीम् अनुगृह्णीष्व निवापदत्तिभिः;<BR>UR. 75.8.: अनुगृहीतो ऽहम् अमुनो ऽपदेशेन;<BR>RAM. I.11.13.: {#anugfhRantu mAm atra BavantaH<BR>SaraRAgatam#}.<BR>c. उप tollere. HIT. 45.12.: {#avyavasAyinam alasam…<BR>pramade 'va hi vfdDapatin ne 'Caty upagfhItuM lakzmIH#};<BR>RAM. III.51.2.: उपगृह्य शिरो राज्ञः.<BR>c. नि<BR>1) deorsum sumere, deorsum tenere. H. 4.18. 19.:<BR>{#vegena prahitam bAhun nijagrAha hasann iva . nigfhya<BR>tam#} etc.<BR>2) deprimere, supprimere, devincere, cohibere.<BR>N. 22.24.: निगृह्या ऽऽत्मनो दुःखम्; MAN. 11.32.:<BR>स्वेनैऽव वीर्येणनिगृह्णीयाद् अरीन्; HIT. 72.10. 67.13.<BR>3) retinere, inhibere, sustinere, sistere, e. c. equos. N. 20.4.:<BR>निगृह्णीष्व…हयान् एतान्.<BR>c. नि praef. वि id. A. 9.9.: {#vinigfhya hayAMScA 'Ta raTaYca<BR>mama#}.<BR>c. नि praef. सम् jaculari, sagittas conjicere, telis petere.<BR>DR. 7.21.: {#raTAnIkaM SaravarzAnDakAraY cakruH krudDAH<BR>sarvataH sannigfhya#}; cf. प्रतिग्रह् et निग्रह्.<BR>c. परि<BR>1) amplecti. SA. 5.101.: {#patim utTApayAmAsa<BR>bAhuByAm parigfhya vE#}.<BR>2) accipere. DR. 4.14.: {#padyam<BR>parigfhARe 'dam AsanaYca#}.<BR>3) inhibere. Lass. 85.9.:<BR>वागर्थम् परिगृह्य मोक्षपदवीन् ध्यायन्ति निर्मत्सराः.<BR>c. प्र tollere, levare, sublevare, protendere. H. 4.17.: {#bAhum<BR>pragfhya…aByadravata…BImasenam#}; DR. 8.4.:<BR>गदाम् प्रगृह्या ऽभ्यद्रवत्; 5.25. A. 5.25. 6.16. 7.11.<BR>c. प्रति<BR>1) prehendere. IN. 2.19.: {#sacE 'nam vfttapInAByAm<BR>bAhuByAm pratyagfhRata#}. (*) RAM. III.56.3.: {#pratijagrAha<BR>jananyAS caraRO#}.<BR>2) accipere. A. 6.24. N. 25.4. 18.;<BR>वाक्यम्, वचनम्, आज्ञाम् प्रतिग्रहीतुम्<BR>sermonem, jussum alicujus accipere, excipere. R. Schl. I.1.22.:<BR>{#Sizyas tu tasya bruvato muner vAkyam anuttamam<BR>. taTe 'ti pratijagrAha#}; 11.18.: {#taTe 'tica nfpasyA<BR>''jYAm mantriRaH pratigfhya te#}.<BR>3) recipere, excipere<BR>hospitio. N. 21.20.: {#tam BImaH pratijagrAha pUjayA<BR>parayA#}. — अस्त्रैः प्रतिग्रहीतुम् sagittis petere. A. 10.28.<BR>— Caus. facere ut aliquis capiat. IN. 3.2.: {#pAdyam AcamanIyaYca<BR>pratigrAhya nfpAtmajam#}.<BR>c. वि<BR>1) capere, prehendere. A. 9.8.: {#antarBUmigatAScA<BR>'nye hayAnAm caraRAny aTa . vyagfhRan#}.<BR>2) pugnare<BR>c. aliquo. HIT. 67.13.: {#kaTam anena balavatA sArdDam<BR>BavAn vigrahItuM samarTaH#}; 118.9.: {#etEH sanDin na<BR>kurvIta vigfhRIyAt tu kevalam#}; A. 10.29.: ततो शरजालेन<BR>…व्यगृह्णं (*) सह दैतेयैः; v. विग्रह.<BR>c. सम्<BR>1) capere, sumere, prehendere. SU. 4.17.: {#gade<BR>BIme saNgfhRItAm uBO tadA#} (omisso augmento).<BR>2) colligere, continere, zusammennehmen, e. c. vestem.<BR>DR. 3.1.: सङ्गृह्णती कौशिकम् उत्तरीयम्.<BR>3) flectere,<BR>moderari, regere, currum, equos. A. 1.2.: {#sa (indravAhaH)<BR>…mAtalisaNgfhItaH#}; 8.19.: {#vftrasya vaDe saNgfhItA<BR>hayA mama#}; 29.: सुसङ्गृहीतैर् हरिभिः.<BR>(*) Nonnunquam etiam in formis gunandis ṛ pro ra invenitur,<BR>ut videtur, propter productam intermediam vocalem;<BR>ita in HIT. 13.6. legitur anugṛhîtum pro aṇugrahîtum;<BR>RAM. III.56.12. gṛhîṣyê pro grahîṣyê.<BR>(**) Sic legendum pro grahiṣyâmi.<BR>(*) Notetur forma pratyagṛhṇata pro pratyagṛhnîta,<BR>correpto charactere nâ ante terminationem gravem<BR>in na pro nî, in analogia linguae graecae, ubi e. c. ἐδάμνατο<BR>opponitur formae activae ἐδάμνη; v. gr. comp. 485.<BR>(*) De formâ vyagṛhṇam pro vyagṛhṇâm v. gr. 324.:<BR>gr. min. 293.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=110-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2940" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रह
ग्रह m. (r. ग्रह् s. अ)<BR>1) actio prehendendi. RAGH. 10.48.<BR>2) solis et lunae eclipsis (v. राहु).<BR>3) cognomen Râhûs.<BR>RAGH. 12.28.<BR>4) planeta. SU. 2.25. N. 13.24.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2941" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रहण
ग्रहण n. (r. ग्रह् s. अन, v. euphon. r. 94^a).) actio capiendi,<BR>prehendendi. IN. 2.25.; नामग्रहण nominis pronunciatio.<BR>RAGH. 7.38.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2942" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्राम
ग्राम m. (ut mihi videtur, e ग्राह्म, ejecto ह्, a r. ग्रह् s. म,<BR>cf. गृह)<BR>1) pagus, vicus. H. 1.39.<BR>2) turba. N. 4.10.<BR>BH. 6.24. BHAR. 3.23. (Fortasse lith. kiếma-s vicus,<BR>ejecto r et mutatâ mediâ in tenuem; hib. gramaisg «the<BR>mub», gramasgar «a flock, company».)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2943" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामिन्
ग्रामिन् m. (a praec. s. इन्) vicanus. N. 13.48.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2944" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रामीण
ग्रामीण Adj. (a ग्राम s. ईन) rusticus. BHAR. 1.89.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2945" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रम्य
ग्रम्य (a ग्राम vicus, s. य) cicur, mansuetus. N. 13.8.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2946" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रावन्
ग्रावन् m. (fortasse a r. ग्रह् s. वन्, ejecto ह्) lapis, saxum,<BR>rupes. BHAR. 3.29. 79. HIT. 43.11. (Lith. riếwa<BR>rupes, abjecto g, hib. creag id. mutato v in g, v. gr.<BR>comp. 19.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2947" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्राह
ग्राह m. (r. ग्रह् s. अ)<BR>1) prehensio.<BR>2) ut videtur, serpens<BR>aquaticus (Wils.: a shark; according to some, the gangetic<BR>alligator, according to others, the water elephant, the<BR>hippopotamus? AM. 3. any large fish or marine animal.).<BR>N. 11.21. 22.23. cf. N. 11.27.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2948" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्राहिन्
ग्राहिन् (r. ग्रह् s. इन्) sumens, prehendens, tenens, in fine<BR>compp. BHAR. 3.67.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2949" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रीवा
ग्रीवा f. (ut videtur, e गीर्वा, quodipsum e गर्वा sive गार्वा,<BR>a r. गॄ s. वा) collum, cervix. (Lith. galwà caput, mutato<BR>r in l, v. गॄ; russ. glavà et golovà id.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2950" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रीष्म
ग्रीष्म Adj. calidus, fervidus. Subst. m.<BR>1) calor, aestas.<BR>2) fervidum anni tempus. RAGH. 16.54. Lass. 50.7.<BR>(Hib. gris ignis, griosgaim «I fry, broil», griosach «burning<BR>embers»; lith. karsz-tas calidus, karsz-tis calor,<BR>karszty-métis fervidum anni tempus.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2951" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रुच्
ग्रुच् 1. P. (चौर्ये) furari, cf. ग्लुच्, ग्लह्, ग्रह्.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2952" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रैव
ग्रैव n. (a ग्रीवा s. अ) collare, catena collaris, praesertim<BR>elephantorum. RAGH. 4.48.: करिणाङ् ग्रैवम्, v. sq.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2953" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्रैवेय
ग्रैवेय n. (a ग्रीवा s. एय) id. RAGH. 4.75.: मातङ्गग्रैवेय;<BR>R. Schl. I.53.17.: {#hiraRyakakzagrEveyAn…dadAmi kuYjarARAn<BR>te sahasrARi caturdaSa#} (*).<BR>(*) Notetur, Adjectivum supra laudatum solo casu convenire<BR>cum substantivo, ad quod pertinet, genere autem cum<BR>illo, ad quod sensu refertur; sic sl. 18.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2954" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्लस्
ग्लस् 1. A. i. q. ग्रस्.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2955" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्लह्
ग्लह् 1. A. i. q. ग्रह्, unde ortum est mutato r in l. (Hib.<BR>glacaim «I accept, receive, take, seize, feel, apprehend».)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2956" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्लह
ग्लह m. (r. ग्लह् s. अ) ludus talarius. MAH. 2.1968.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2957" target="_blank">Correction</a>

