ग्लान v. ग्लै.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2958" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्लानि
ग्लानि f. (a r. ग्लै s. नि pro ति, gr. 645.)<BR>1) fatigatio, lassitudo,<BR>languor. SA. 5.27. BH. 4.7.<BR>2) tristitia. BHAR. 1.45.:<BR>मुदञ्च ग्लानिञ्च कथयति पथिषु.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2959" target="_blank">Correction</a>

ग्लास्नु
ग्लास्नु (r. ग्लै s. स्नु, fem. स्नु) fessus, defessus, lassus, fatigatus.<BR>AM. (Cf. lat. lassus, quod fortasse e glassus, sicut<BR>natus e gnatus; glassus vero per assimilationem ortum<BR>esse potest e glasnus, quod sanscrite ग्लस्नस् sonaret.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=112-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=2960" target="_blank">Correction</a>

