जटा
जटा f. (r. जट् s. आ) coma implicata, involuta (*). SU. 1.8.<BR>(*) Wils.: The hair matted as worn by the god Siwa,<BR>and by ascetics; the long hairs occasionally clotted together,<BR>and brought over the head, so as to project like a<BR>horn from the forehead, at other times allowed to fall<BR>carelessly over the back and shoulders.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=133-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=3348" target="_blank">Correction</a>

