तृण n. (r. तृण् s. अ nisi, quod Benfeyus putat, तृण corruptum [Page156-b+ 37]<BR>e तृह्ण, ita ut ad 2. तृंह् crescere pertineat)<BR>1) gramen.<BR>2) arundo? v. sq. BR. 3.23. N. 13.28. (Cum<BR>तृण e तर्ण cf. goth. thaurnu-s euphonice pro thurnus<BR>(gr. comp. 82.), utroque a attenuato in u; nostrum<BR>Dorn; russ. tern id.; hib. dreas, dris «a briar, bramble».)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=156-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=3829" target="_blank">Correction</a>

