दिव्
1. दिव् 4. P. दीव्यामि (gr. 332.), Part. pass. द्यूत, praet.<BR>mltf. अदेविषम्<BR>1) splendere (v. 3. {#div, diva,<BR>divan, divas#} et cf. दीप्).<BR>2) ludere. N. 7.4.: {#ehi<BR>dIvya nalena vE#}. C. instr. rei, de quâ luditur, MAH. 2.261.:<BR>{#etad rAjan mama Danan tena dIvyAmy ahan<BR>tvayA#}. C. dat. rei, MAH. 1.1192.: {#ehi sArdDam mayA<BR>dIvya dAsIBAvAya BAmini#}; 2.2468.: {#punar dIvyAma<BR>Badran te vanavAsAya pARqavEH#}. — Part. praes. A.<BR>N. 7.10.: दीव्यमानम् अरिन्दमम्. — वाणान् देवितुम्<BR>tela emittere. BHATT. 5.81. (Huc trahi posset lat.<BR>lu-do, mutato d in l, cf. द्यूत ludus; Pottius confert jocus<BR>quod e djo-cus explicari potest sicut Jupiter, Jovis e<BR>Djupiter, Djovis (v. gr. comp. 122.); lith. jůkas jocus,<BR>jůkoju jocor. Quae ad दिव् splendere referendae sunt<BR>voces v. s. दिव, दिवस, द्यु, द्यो. Fortasse etiam lith.<BR>źibbu splendeo huc pertinet.)<BR>c. परि Part. pass. परिद्यून moestus, tristis. MAH. 3.306. 12433.<BR>R. Schl. II.47.2. 72.50. Cf. देव्.<BR>c. प्रति ludere cum aliquo, c. acc. pers. MAH. 3.1356.:<BR>माङ् कितवः प्रत्यदेवीत्. — ATM. MAH. 2.2057.: {#yena<BR>mAn tvam mahArAja Danena pratidIvyase#}.<BR>c. वि lusu perdere. MAH. 2.2384.: {#imAM saBAmaDye yo<BR>vyadevId glahezu#}.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=168-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=4077" target="_blank">Correction</a>

दिव्
2. दिव् 10. P. देवयामि (proprie Caus. praec.) vexare;<BR>queri, lamentari. Cf. देव्.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=168-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=4078" target="_blank">Correction</a>

