पर्वन्
पर्वन् n. (r. पर्व् s. अन्) Wilsonus explicat:<BR>1) a knot, a<BR>joint in a cane or body etc.<BR>2) a name given to certain<BR>days in the lunar month, as the full and change of the<BR>moon and the 6th, 8th and 10th of each half month.<BR>3) Particular periods of the year, as the equinox, solstice<BR>etc.<BR>4) the moment of the sun's entering a new sign.<BR>5) a festival, a holiday.<BR>6) Opportunity, occasion. MED.<BR>7) a chapter, a book, the division of a work. OR. D.<BR>8) a<BR>moment, an instant SABD. CH. SA. 1.25. UR. 70.15.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=213-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5018" target="_blank">Correction</a>

