1. पश् 1. P. A. 10. P. (पशामि, पशे, पाशयामि) ligare.<BR>(V. पाश et cf. पष्, स्पश्; cambro-brit. fasgu<BR>«to bind, or tie in a bundle», fasgiad «a ligation, a<BR>tying in a bundle»; gr. πήγνυμι; lat. pango, fascia, fortasse<BR>etiam fas huc pertinet sicut jus a Pottio apte ad<BR>यु ligare refertur; russ. pojas cingulum, nisi po est<BR>praep.; v. Pott. 1.267.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=213-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5035" target="_blank">Correction</a>

