भक्षक m. (r. भक्ष् s. अक) edens. HIT. 75.8.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=241-1b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5764" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भक्ष्य
भक्ष्य (r. भक्ष् s. य)<BR>1) Adj. edendus.<BR>2) m. cibus. H. 2.8.<BR>N. 9.13. (Goth. basi, them. basja n. bacca.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=241-1b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5765" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भग
भग m. (r. भज् s. अ)<BR>1) portio.<BR>2) bona fortuna, felicitas,<BR>beatitudo.<BR>3) vulva. AM. (Huc vel ad भाग traxerim<BR>goth. ga-bigs dives, ita ut proprie significet qui cum<BR>divitiis est, them. ga-biga = सभग; cf. etiam lith.<BR>nabagas homo miser, pauper, na = scr. न non; bagotas<BR>dives; russ. û-bogiĭ pauper, bogatyĭ dives; cf. Pott. pp. 235. 236.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=241-1b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5766" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भगवत्
भगवत् (a भग s. वत्) felix, beatus, excelsus, excellens,<BR>praeclarus, venerabilis. SU. 3.24. 4.23. BH. 10.14. RAGH. 8.80.<BR>(Cf. slav. bog deus.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=242-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5767" target="_blank">Correction</a>

