भुवन n. (r. भू s. अन, omisso Gunae incremento, v. euph.<BR>r. 51.) mundus. RAGH. 1.26.: भुवनद्वय mundorum par<BR>i. e. coelum et terra; RAGH. 2.53. N. 24.33. MEGH. 6.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=248-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5884" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भू
1. भू 1. P. A. (भवामि, भवे; अभूवम् (gr. 414.), {#aBavizi;<BR>baBUva, baBUve#} (gr. 445.); भविष्यामि, भविष्ये)<BR>1) esse, existere. BH. 16.13.: {#idam api me Bavizyati<BR>punar Danam#}; N. 10.22.: कथम् बुद्ध्वा भविष्यति. — Cum<BR>antecedente न mori. H. 4.50.: अद्य न भविष्यसि;<BR>N. 21.10.: न भविष्याम्य् असंशयम्.<BR>2) esse ut verb.<BR>substant. BR. 3.18.: भविष्यामि सुखान्विता; N. 1.28.:<BR>सफलन् ते भवेज् जन्म; BR. 3.8.: {#tat tezAm vipriyam<BR>Bavet#}; 12.: अनाथा कृपणा…भविष्यामि. — Cum<BR>dat. esse alicui rei, praeditum esse aliquâ re. BR. 3.19.:<BR>{#devASca pitaraSca…tvayA dattena toyena Bavizyanti<BR>hitAya#}. Causam esse alicujus rei. MAH. 3.12312.:<BR>त्रैलोक्यस्य…भवन्ति स्म विनाशाय. — Pass.<BR>impers. c. instrum. pers. et praedic. HIT. 17.20.: {#aDunA<BR>tavA 'nucareRa mayA sarvadA Bavitavyam#}; UR. 38.3.infr.:<BR>प्रत्यासन्नेन चन्द्रेण भवितव्यम्.<BR>3) fieri, oriri.<BR>BH. 14.17.: प्रमादमोहौ तमसो भवतः; N. 23.11.: {#te<BR>tenA'vekzitAH kumBAH pUrRA evA 'Bavas tataH#}; A. 3.27.:<BR>तस्य तच् छतधा रूपम् अभवत्; MAH. 1.1501.: {#BasmasAd<BR>Bavet#}. — Part. pass. भूत<BR>1) qui est, existit.<BR>SU. 1.25.: त्रिषु लोकेषु यद् भूतङ् किञ्चित् स्थावरजङ्गमम्.<BR>In fine comp. N. 12.38.: {#asyA 'raRyasya mahataH<BR>ketuBUtam ivo 'cCritam (Siloccayam)#}.<BR>2) factus.<BR>A. 3.28.: {#punas tAni SarIrARi ekIBUtAni BArata<BR>. adfSyanta#}. — भूत subst. n. creatura, animans,<BR>res. H. 4.32. SU. 2.7. BH. 2.69. N. 14.2. BH. 7.26. — Caus.<BR>भावय्<BR>1) facere ut alqs existat, sustentare, nutrire.<BR>MAH. 3.8763.: {#tA (prajAH) BAvitA BAvayanti<BR>havyakavyEr divOkasaH#}; BH. 3.11.: {#devAn BAvayatA<BR>'nena te devAH BAvayantu vaH . parasparam BAvayantaH<BR>SreyaH param avApsyaTa#}.<BR>2) cogitare, meditari (secundum<BR>gramm. Ind. भू cl. 10.). BH. 2.66.: {#nA 'sti budDir ayuktasya<BR>nacA 'yuktasya BAvanA . nacA 'BAvayataH SAntiMH#};<BR>R. Schl. II.67.20.: भावयन्न् आत्मना ऽऽत्मानम्.<BR>— Desid. 1. esse, existere velle. MAH. 4.678.: {#na tizWati<BR>sma sanmArge naca Darme buBUzati#}.<BR>2) eligere conjugem.<BR>MAH. 1.7068.: {#yadi kanye 'yan naca kaYcid<BR>buBUzati#}; 7969.: को बुभूषेत ना ऽर्जुनम्. (Lat. fu-i,<BR>fu-turus, fo-re; -bam (ama-bam) = अभवम्, -bo, -bimus<BR>= भविष्यामि, भविष्यामस्, v. gr. comp. 526. 662.;<BR>gr. ϕύ-ω, ἔϕῡ-ν, ἔϕῡ-ς, ἔϕῡ = {#aBUvam, aBUs,<BR>aBUt#}, v. gr. comp. 573.; lith. bú-ti esse, bu-waú<BR>fui = अभवम्, bú-su ero = भविष्यामि, v. gr. comp. 522. 652.;<BR>slav. by-ti esse, bû-dû ero; germ. vet. bim sum,<BR>nostrum bin, bir-u-mês sumus = भवामस्, mutato v in<BR>r, v. gr. comp. 20.; hib. fuilim sum, ba me vel budh me<BR>fui, proprie fuit ego, ba = अभवत्, budh = अभूत्.<BR>Ad Caus. भावयामि traxerim lat. facio mutato v in c<BR>sicut e. c. in vic-si, vic-tum, v. gr. comp. 19.; fê-mina,<BR>quae procreat, gignit, suff. mina = माना, gr. μενη,<BR>sicut mini formarum ut ama-mini = मानास्, μενοι,<BR>v. gr. comp. 478.; fê-tus, fe-tura; goth. baua aedifico,<BR>bauais aedificas, ubi ai = अय τοῦ भावयसि, v. gr.<BR>comp. 109^a).6. et cf. scr. भवन domus.)<BR>c. अनु<BR>1) adesse, interesse. N. 5.40.: अनुभूया ऽस्य विवाहम्.<BR>2) percipere, sentire, experiri, perpeti. RAGH. 1.21.:<BR>असक्तः सुखम् अन्वभूत्; 8.3.: अनुभूय…अभिषेचनम्;<BR>MAH. 3.10789.: {#IdfSIm Apadam ko 'tra<BR>dvitIyo 'nuBavizyati#}.<BR>c. अनु praef. सम् id. RAGH. 9.48.: आर्तवम् उत्सवं समनुभूय.<BR>c. अन्तर् inesse. MAN. 12.87.<BR>c. अभि aggredi, accedere. MAH. 3.10592.: {#ezA te BAsvatI<BR>kIrtir lokAn aBiBavizyati#}; BH. 1.40.:<BR>धर्मे नष्टे कुलङ् कृत्स्नम् अधर्मो ऽभिभवति. Hostiliter<BR>aggredi, invadere. SAK. 15.3.infr.: {#paritrAyeTAm<BR>mAm anena duzwamaDukareRA 'BiBUyamAnAm#}.<BR>2) superare,<BR>vincere. A. 3.30.: {#yadA 'BiBavitum vAREr naca<BR>Saknomi tam#}; 11.2.: {#na tvA 'BiBavituM Sakto mAnuzo<BR>Buvi kaScana#}.<BR>c. उत् Caus. facere ut alqs existat, procreare. RAGH. 2.62.:<BR>मायाम् उद्भाव्य.<BR>c. उत् praef. सम् oriri. GHAT. 5.: शोकः समुद्भवति.<BR>c. तिरस् evanescere. RAGH. 16.23.: पूर् अपि…तिरोबभूव.<BR>Caus. delere, evertere, frangere. R. Schl. I.44.9.:<BR>{#tasyA 'valepanam…tiroBAvayitum budDiY<BR>cakre#}.<BR>c. परा perire. MAH. 1.4167.: यथा धर्मो न पराभवेत्.<BR>c. परि despicere, contemnere. HIT. 30.11.: {#SaSinas<BR>tulyavaMSo 'pi nirDanaH pariBUyate#}; DR. 6.17.: {#paYce<BR>'ndrakalpAn pariBUya#}; BR. 2.16.<BR>c. परि praef. सम् id. MAH. 3.13230.<BR>c. प्र<BR>1) esse. BH. 16.9.: प्रभवन्त्य् उग्रकर्माणः.<BR>2) fieri,<BR>prodire, oriri, nasci. BH. 8.18.: {#avyaktAd vyaktayaH<BR>sarvAH praBavanty aharAgame#}; RAGH. 10.51.: {#puruzaH prabaBUvA<BR>'gneH#}; HIT. 13.8.: लोभात् क्रोधः प्रभवति.<BR>3) valere, praevalere, potentem, parem esse, c. dat. vel<BR>infin. HIT. 25.6.: प्रीत्यै (चेतसः) सज्जनभाषितम् प्रभवति;<BR>UR. 7.9.: {#kaTam…nirmAtum praBaven manoharam<BR>idaM rUpam purARo muniH#}; RAGH. 8.44. R. Schl. II.23.38.<BR>— Cum gen. pers. MAN. 5.2.: {#viprARAM svaDarmam<BR>anutizWatAN kaTam mftyur praBavati#}; MAH. 3.12669.:<BR>ना ऽस्माकम् मृत्युर् प्रभवते. — Absol. HIT. 24.3.:<BR>{#viSvAsAt praBavanty ete viSvAsas tatra no<BR>'citaH#}. — प्रभवत् praevalens, praepotens. H. 2.32.<BR>4) abundare. प्रभूत abundans, multus, copiosus. N. 13.3.:<BR>प्रभूतयवसेन्धनम्; HIT. 45.6.: प्रभूते ऽपि वित्ते.<BR>c. वि Caus. proprie facere ut aliquid foras sit, inde<BR>1) explorare, investigare, indagare. MAN. 8.25.: {#vAhyEr<BR>viBAvayel liNgEr BAvam antargatan nfRAm#} (Schol.<BR>निरूपयेत्).<BR>2) probare, demonstrare. MAN. 8.56.:<BR>उक्तञ्च न विभावयेत्.<BR>3) observare, percipere, sentire.<BR>MAN. 7.147.: मन्त्रयेद् अविभावितः; RAGH. 11.10.:<BR>उह्यमान इव वाहनोचितः पादचारम् अपि न व्यभावयत्.<BR>— Pass. videri. MAH. 1.932.: {#sUryAMSuBiH<BR>spfzwaM sarvaM Suci viBAvyate#}. HIT. 124.63.<BR>c. सम्<BR>1) una esse, conjunctum esse. SU. 2.11.: {#tezAm<BR>…samBUya sarvEr asmABiH kAryaH sarvAtmanA vaDaH#}.<BR>Coire cum femina. MAH. 1.4398.: सम्बभूव तया सह.<BR>2) fieri. SU. 1.30.: {#tatas tO tu jawA BittvA mOlinO<BR>sambaBUvatuH#}; 4.11.: {#dfzwvE 'va tAm varArohAm vyaTitO<BR>sambaBUvatuH#}; MAH. 3.8843.: गर्भिण्यौ सम्बभूवतुः;<BR>3.16478.: तथा समभवच्चा ऽपि यद् उवाच विभीषणः.<BR>3) oriri. H. 1.17.: घोरा समभवत् सन्ध्या;<BR>BR. 3.24.: हर्षः समभवद् महान्.<BR>4) nasci, c. ablat.<BR>patris et loc. matris. MAH. 1.8028.: {#sAttvatyAm atiraTaH<BR>sambaBUva DanaYjayAt#}.<BR>5) esse posse, sufficiens<BR>spatium habere in aliquo loco, valere. M. 12.: {#aliYjare<BR>yadAcE 'va nA 'sO samaBavat#}. — Caus.<BR>1) facere ut<BR>alqs existat, sustentare, servare. MAN. 2.142.: {#yaH…<BR>samBAvayaticA 'nnena#}; MAH. 1.1343.: {#samBAvayA ''tmAnam<BR>ajIrRam mama tejasA#}.<BR>2) facere. MAH. 3.13316.:<BR>स्वस्तिवाचनम् समभावयम्; 13317.: {#svastivAcanAni<BR>suzwu samBAvitAni#}.<BR>3) committere. MAH. 1.2088.:<BR>सम्भावय…मयि सर्वम्.<BR>4) convenire, congredi,<BR>adire. MAH. 3.1982.: {#kAmyake pArTAn samaBAvayad<BR>acyutaH#}; UR. 9.6.infr.<BR>5) cogitare. RAGH. 7.6.:<BR>सम्भावितः (Schol. चिन्तितः).<BR>6) putare, existimare.<BR>RAGH. 6.42.: धारां शितां रामपरश्वधस्य सम्भावयत्य्<BR>उत्पलपत्रसाराम्.<BR>7) magni aestimare, honorare. BH. 2.34.:<BR>सम्भावितस्य (Schol. बहुमतस्य); RAGH. 10.56.:<BR>सम्भावितान् ताभ्यां सुमित्राम्; 5.11.: {#prApto 'si<BR>samBAvayitum vanAn mAm#}. Cum instr. honestare,<BR>dignari, colere, ornare alquâ re. RAGH. 16.40.: {#anyEr<BR>anujIvilokaM samBAvayAmAsa gfhEH#} (Schol. सत्कृतवान्);<BR>7.8.: विलोचनन् दक्षिणम् अञ्जनेन सम्भाव्य<BR>(Schol. अलङ्कृत्य).<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=248-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5885" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भू
2. भू f. (a r. भू) terra. H. 2.18. SU. 2.24. (V. भूमि.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5886" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूतपूर्व
भूतपूर्व (e भूत qui fuit et पूर्व prior, loco Adverbii पूर्वम्<BR>prius, antea, v. gr. 680.) prior. BR. 1.22.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5887" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूति
भूति f. (r. भू s. ति)<BR>1) existentia. DR. 5.9.<BR>2) felicitas,<BR>prosperitas, salus. RAGH. 1.18. 10.59.<BR>3) succus, qui<BR>ex elephantorum temporibus fluit. MEGH. 19. (Gr.<BR>ϕύσις e ϕύτις.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5888" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूधर
भूधर m. (terram ferens e भू et धर) mons. IN. 5.10.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5889" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूभृत्
भूभृत् m. (terram ferens, sustinens e भू et भृत्)<BR>1) mons. MED.<BR>2) rex. Up. 79. RAGH. 11.81.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5890" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमि
भूमि f. (r. भू s. मि)<BR>1) terra. IN. 1.31.<BR>2) locus. RAGH. 4.42. 6.31.<BR>(Cf. lat. humus, hib. uim «the earth, a<BR>country».)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5891" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूमिका
भूमिका f. (a praec. s. क in fem.) in linguâ scenicâ partes,<BR>Rolle. UR. 35.4.infr.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5892" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूय
भूय n. (r. भू s. य) substantia. BH. 14.26. 18.53.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5893" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूयस्
भूयस् (Compar. τοῦ बहु, ejecto अ, correpto ब् + ह् in<BR>भ्, suff. यस् pro ईयस्, v. gr. 251. annot. et 234.)<BR>1) Adj. πλείων. BR. 2.6. N. 18.19.<BR>2) Adv. a) plus. N. 8.14.b)<BR>iterum, denuo. BR. 1.11. N. 23.2. 24.2. 25.5.<BR>BH. 2.20.: ना ऽयम् भूत्वा भविता वा न भूयः «non<BR>ille extitit, existetque non iterum». — Instr. भूयसा<BR>nimis. RAGH. 8.9. (Hib. bhus «a sign of the comparative<BR>degree, and has always ni before it, as ni bhus airde<BR>higher».)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5894" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूयिष्ठ
भूयिष्ठ (Superl. τοῦ बहु v. praec. et gr. 251. annot.) plurimus,<BR>permultus. H. 1.19. — भूयिष्ठम् Adv.<BR>1) valde,<BR>admodum; prorsus, plane, omnino. RAGH. 13.14. DR. 8.40.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5895" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूरि
भूरि multus, praesertim in initio compp. e. c. भूरितेजस् magnum<BR>splendorem, magnam vim habens. MAH. 1.3849.;<BR>v. sq. (Huc traxerim gr. μῡϱίος, mutato भ् in nasalem<BR>ejusdem organi; huc etiam trahi possent hib. mor et lat.<BR>mul-tus, nisi pertinent ad पुरु q. v.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5896" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूरिदक्षिण
भूरिदक्षिण (BAH. e भूरि et दक्षिणा q. v.) multa dona sacrificalia<BR>habens vel praebens. N. 12.14. IN. 1.16. A. 2.8.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5897" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूर्ज
भूर्ज m. nomen arboris (Wils. «The Bhôj or Bhôjpatr,<BR>a tree growing in the snowy mountains, and called by<BR>travellers a kind of birch; the bark is used for writing<BR>on»). RAGH. 4.73. UR. 24.15.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5898" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूष्
भूष् 1. et 10. P. ornare. R. Schl. II.39.17.: {#BUzayAmAsa<BR>gAtrARi tEr…viBUzaREH#}; I.48.5.: {#BUzayantAv iman<BR>deSaY candrasUryAv ivA 'mbaram#}; H. 2.23.: दिव्याभरणभूषिता.<BR>(Hib. beosaighim «I ornament, deck<BR>out, beautify» = भूषयामि; huc, vel ad भूषण q. v., trahi<BR>potest lat. orno abjectâ initiali; respicias formam osnamentum<BR>apud Varr. et hornamentum pro fornamentum<BR>in inscript. apud Gruter.)<BR>c. वि i. q. simpl. IN. 1.9.: हेमविभूषितम्.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5899" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भूषण
भूषण n. (r. भूष् s. अन, v. euph. r. 94^a).) ornamentum. N. 9.5.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5900" target="_blank">Correction</a>

भृ
भृ 1. et 3. P. A. (भरामि, भरे, बिभर्मि, विभ्रे; praet. redupl.<BR>बभार, बभ्रे vel बिभराञ्चकार, -चक्रे)<BR>1) Cl. 3. ferre,<BR>gestare, gerere. A. 1.3.: नवान्य् आभरणानि बिभ्रत्;<BR>RAGH. 18.44.: धुरम् धरित्र्या बिभराम्बभूव; BH. 15.17.:<BR>यो लोकत्रयम् आविश्य बिभर्त्य् अव्यय ईश्वरः; H. 3.14.:<BR>ताम्…मानुषरूपम् बिभ्रतीम्; N. 13.52.: {#biBarzi<BR>paramam vapuH#}; MAN. 2.157.: नाम बिभ्रति.<BR>2) Cl. 1. et 3.<BR>sustentare, nutrire. N. 17.41.: {#BartavyA…patnI<BR>hi patinA#}; HIT. 1.13.: दरिद्रान् भर; MAH. 1.3042.:<BR>{#aRqAni biBrati svAni pipIlikAH; na BareTAH kaTan<BR>nu svam Atmajam#}.<BR>3) Cl. 1. A. mercede conducere<BR>alqm. (v. भृति, भृत्य). N. 15.4.: भरस्व माम्.<BR>(Gr. ϕέϱω; lat. fero, fer-s, fer-t, fer-tis = {#BiBarzi,<BR>biBarti, biBfTa#}, abjectâ syllabâ redupl.; for-tis; fortasse<BR>por-to e for-to; etiam pario, nisi pertinet ad कृ, huc trahi<BR>posset, mutatâ aspiratâ in tenuem; fortasse vi-bro = भृ<BR>praef. वि; goth. BAR ferre, bar tulit, tulit, baira fero;<BR>germ. vet. bëro pario, bur-di onus; fortasse etiam goth.<BR>BRAH afferre (brigga, brah-ta, nostrum bringe) huc<BR>pertinet, adjectâ gutturali, ita bairga occulo, cf. निभृत<BR>occultus; v. Graff. 3.139.; fortasse goth. bairg mons a<BR>ferendo dictum est sicut scr. bhUdhara, bhUbhRt, mahIdhara et<BR>aliae quae tam terram sustentans quam mons significant<BR>voces; hib. beirim «I bear, carry»; slav. brjemja<BR>onus.)<BR>c. नि निभृत occultus. N. 17.91.: निभृतो ऽग्निः; RAGH. 8.15.:<BR>नभसा निभृतेन्दुना; HIT. 21.8.: {#jambukena suniBftam<BR>uktam#}.<BR>c. सम्<BR>1) comportare. R. Schl. I.11.13.: {#samBriyantAM<BR>samBArAH#}; II.56.8.: {#maDUni maDukAriBiH samBftAni<BR>nage nage#}. — सम्भृत compositus. HIT. 124.13.: {#paYcaBiH<BR>samBfte dehe#}.<BR>2) sustentare. R. Schl. I.52.8.: {#kaccit<BR>te samBftA BftyAH#}.<BR>3) perficere, peragere. RAGH. 11.32.:<BR>सम्भृतक्रतुः (Schol. सम्पादितयज्ञोपकरणः).<BR>Parare. UR. 93.3.: {#upanIyatAm mantreRa samBftaH kumArasyA<BR>'BizekaH#}. — Caus. comportari jubere. R. Schl. I.11.3.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=250-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=5901" target="_blank">Correction</a>

