2. मिष् 6. P. (स्पधीयाम् K. स्पर्धे V.) aemulari, certare. — Part.<BR>praes. in gen. abso. invito. MAH. 1.7179.:<BR>{#tO pArTivAnAm mizatAn narendra kfzRAm upAdAya<BR>gatO narAgryO#}; 8159.: {#tvan Dakzyase 'naGa kARqavan<BR>dAvam adyE 'va mizato 'sya SacIpateH#}; 2.2535.: {#DArtarAzwrAn<BR>raRe hatvA mizatAM sarvaDanvinAm SamaN gantAsmi<BR>na cirAt#}; 3.10464.: {#tena dvAdaSavArzikyAm<BR>anAvfzwyAm mahAtmanA vfzwam…mizato vajrapARinaH#}.<BR>(V. praef. उत् et नि et cf. मील्; russ. migaju et<BR>mischu nictor; lith. mirkloju id., mếgmi dormio; fortasse<BR>lat. nico, nic-to e nimic-0, nimic-to = निमिषामि. — Benfey<BR>huc trahit lat. micare.)<BR>c. उत् aperire oculos, proprie aufschlagen. BH. 5.9.:<BR>उन्मिषन् निमिषन्न् अपि.<BR>c. नि claudere oculos, proprie niederschlagen. MAH. 3.10649.:<BR>मत्स्यः सुप्तो न निमिषति.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=264-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=6238" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मिह्
मिह् 1. P. मेहामि, fut. aux. मेक्ष्यामि, part. pass. मीढ<BR>(gr. 102.) Effundere, praesertim mingere. R. Schl. II.75.21.:<BR>सूर्यम् प्रति मेहतु; MAN. 4.52.: {#praty agnim prati<BR>sUryaYca…mehataH#}. (Cf. मिन्व्, lat. mingo, mejo; gr.<BR>ὀ-μιχέω, μοιχός, μοιχάω; lith. myźu mingo, mếszlas<BR>fimus, mếźu stercus egero, mig-la nebula, v. मेघ; anglo-sax.<BR>MIG mingere, mîge, mâh, migon; island. vet.<BR>MIG id.; goth. maihs-tus fimus, adjectâ sibilante; nostrum<BR>Mist.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=264-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=6239" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मी
1. मी 9. P. A. मीनामि, मीने, in dial. Vêd. मिनामि, मिने<BR>(हिंसायाम् K. वधे V.) Ferire, occidere, delere.<BR>RIGV. 71.10.: रूपञ् जरिमा मिनाति; 92.12.: {#aminatI<BR>dEvyAni vratAni#}; 117.3.: {#minantA (= minantO)<BR>dasyor aSivasya mAyAH#}. — Part. pass. मीन.<BR>c. आ i. q. simpl. RIGV. 79.2.: {#A te suparRA aminanta<BR>evEH#} «tuae bene alatae luces feriunt nubem cum properantibus<BR>ventis». ATM. sibi mutuo aliquid delere. RIGV. 113.2.:<BR>द्यावा वर्णञ् चरत आमिमाने «coelum percurrunt<BR>(nox et aurora) suum mutuo colorem delentes».<BR>c. प्र i. q. simpl. RIGV. 32.4.: {#mAyinAm aminAH pro 'ta<BR>mAyAH#} «praestigiatorum fregisti praestigias»; 25.1. 92.11.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=265-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=6240" target="_blank">Correction</a>

मी
2. मी 4. A. perire. RIGV. V. (v. Westerg.): {#durmitrAso mimAnA<BR>jahur BojanA#}. — Caus. मापयामि, v. gr. 521.<BR>(Cf. म्रिये morior, unde fortasse मीये ejecto र्<BR>producto इ.)<BR>c. प्र perire, mori. MAN. 9.247.: बालाश्च न प्रमीयन्ते;<BR>R. Schl. II.75.28.: अनपत्यः प्रमीयताम्. प्रमीत mortuus.<BR>MAN. 3.245. — Caus. occidere, delere. MAN. 1.57.:<BR>{#idaM sarvaY carAcaraM saYjIvayaticA 'jasram pramApayaticA<BR>'vyayaH#}; 8.295.: स चेत्…प्रमापयेत् प्राणभृतः;<BR>11.89. 129. MAH. 3.13322.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=265-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=6241" target="_blank">Correction</a>

