म्लेच्छ
म्लेच्छ m. (r. म्लेछ् s. अ, nisi potius म्लेछ् est Denom. a<BR>म्लेच्छ) barbarus, externus (Wils.: The generic term for<BR>a barbarian or foreigner; that is for one speaking any<BR>language but sanscrit, and not subject to the usual Hindu<BR>institutions.). SU. 2.8.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=273-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=6413" target="_blank">Correction</a>

म्लेच्छ्|म्लेछ्
म्लेछ् 1. et 10. P. (अव्यक्तायाम् वाचि K. देश्योक्तौ V.)<BR>indistincte, non perspicue loqui, linguâ terrae alicujus<BR>propriâ, barbarâ, vernaculâ uti. MAH. 2.2040.:<BR>नार्या म्लेछन्ति भाषाभिः.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=273-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=6414" target="_blank">Correction</a>

