1. राज् 1. P. A.<BR>1) splendere. N. 1.12.: {#tatra sma rAjate BEmI…vidyut<BR>sOdAminI yaTA#}; IN. 5.11.: {#sUkzmavastraDaraM<BR>reje jaGanan niravadyayA#} (रेजे gr. 441.); R. Schl. I.1.32.:<BR>चित्रकूटो रराज. In dial. Vêd. etiam. cl. 2.<BR>RIGV. 104.4.: राष्टि.<BR>2) c. gen. in dial. Vêd. regere, imperare.<BR>RIGV. 25.20.: {#tvaM viSvasya moDira divaSca gmaSca<BR>rAjasi#} «tu universi, sapiens! coelique terraeque imperium<BR>habes»; 36.12. (V. राजन् et cf. रञ्ज्, भ्राज्;<BR>lat. rego, rex; goth. raginô rego, impero, servatâ mediâ<BR>sicut in BUG = भुज्; reiki, them. reikja n. imperium<BR>= राज्य, attenuato â in ei i. e. î; reik-s princeps; germ.<BR>vet. rîchi dives.)<BR>c. अभि splendere. MAH. 3.10960.<BR>c. वि id. MAH. 3.8106.: विराजति यथा सोमो मेघैर् मुक्तः;<BR>IN. 5.6. N. 12.37. — Caus. facere ut alqus splendeat,<BR>collustrare. R. Schl. II.26.2.: {#virAjayan rAjasuto<BR>rAjamArgam#}; II.39.18.: व्यराजयत…वेश्म तत्. - विराजित<BR>collustratus, splendens, splendidus. N. 5.3.<BR>c. सम् in dial. Vêd. regere, imperare. RIGV. 27.1.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=288-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=6657" target="_blank">Correction</a>

