लप् 1. P.<BR>1) loqui. GITA-G. 1.41.: {#lapituN kim api<BR>SrutimUle#}.<BR>2) queri, lamentari. NALOD. 3.27.: ललाप<BR>(schol. विललाप.). — Intens. queri, lamentari. MAH. 3.10200.:<BR>लालप्यै ऽव सकरुणम्; R. Schl. II.75.45.: {#lAlapyamAnasya…muhurmuhur<BR>niHSvasataSca GarmaM sA tasya<BR>Sokena jagAma rAtriH#}; MAH. 1.968.: {#lAlapyatas tasya<BR>BAryArTe duHKitasyaca#} (लालप्यतस् pro लालप्यमानस्यं,<BR>v. gr. 597.); 1.4168. 6557. 8449. (Cf. रप्, hib. labhraim<BR>«I say, speak», labhradh «speech, speaking, discoruse»;<BR>lat. loquor, mutato p in qu sicut e. c. in quinque = पञ्च;<BR>lâ-mentum, gr. λάλος, λαλέω per redupl., abjectâ radicis<BR>litterâ finali; lith. lêpju jubeo. Huc etiam pertinere<BR>videntur nonnullae quae labium vel lambare significant<BR>voces: lith. lupa labium, russ. ruba, pers. leb, lat. labium,<BR>labrum, lambo; anglo-sax. lapie lambo, germ. vet. laffu<BR>lambo, lefs labium; v. लपन.)<BR>c. अप recusare, denegare. R. Schl. II.75.24.: यज्ञदक्षिणाम्.<BR>c. आ loqui, alloqui. DR. 3.3.: {#araRye kaTam ekam ekA<BR>tvAm Alapeyam#}.<BR>c. प्र<BR>1) loqui. BH. 5.9.<BR>2) blaterare, garrire. SAK. 32.3.:<BR>प्रलपत्य् एष वैधेयः.<BR>3) lamentari. R. Schl. II.64.1.<BR>4) cum lamentatione alloqui aliquem, c. acc. MAH. 2.2339.:<BR>{#tAm…pralapantIM sma pARqavAn duHSAsanaH<BR>saBAmaDye vicakarza#}.<BR>c. वि queri, lamentari. H. 1.28.: शोकपरीतात्मा विललाप.<BR>ATM. N. 21.16.: एवं विलपमाना. Trans.<BR>1) cum<BR>lamentatione eloqui aliquid. MAH. 2.2343.: {#patitA vilalApe<BR>'dam#}; N. 13.43.: एवमादीनि…विलप्य वराङ्गना प्रलापानि.<BR>2) lamentari, deplorare aliquem.<BR>R. Schl. I.1.33.: विलपन् सुतम्.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=297-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=6817" target="_blank">Correction</a>

