वे 1. P. 9. A. (तन्तुसन्ताने K. स्यूंतौ V.; anom., v. gr. 451. 473. 502. 519. 610.)<BR>texere, suere. RIGV. 61.8.: {#indrAyA<BR>'rkam ahihatya UvuH#} «Indrae hymnum propter Ahis<BR>caedem texuerunt». (Cf. ऊय्, lat. vieo, gr. ἤ-τϱιον, lith.<BR>u-dis textura (= ऊति actio texendi), áu-dźiu texo; hib.<BR>fighim «I weave, plait, twist», figh-te «woven, context»<BR>(gh = य् τοῦ वयामि), fuaghaim «I sew, stitch»;<BR>germ. vet. WAB texere - wiba, wab, wâbumes - retulerim<BR>ad वापयामि, sicut sanscrite secundum generalem<BR>regulam sonaret Caus., pro quo anomale वाययामि, v.<BR>gr. 519.)<BR>c. प्र assuere, affigere. BH. 7.7.: {#mayi sarvam idam protam<BR>sUtre maRigaRA iva#}; MAH. 1.4316.: {#sa rakziBis<BR>tEr ajYAtaH SUle proto mahAtapAH#}. Transfigere. RAGH. 9.75.:<BR>शल्यप्रोतम् प्रेक्ष्य…मुनिपुत्रम् (schol. {#vARAgreRa<BR>syUtam#}).<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=335-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=7553" target="_blank">Correction</a>

