सव्य
सव्य laevus, sinister. (Slav. ṣûi id., Them. ṣûjo, fem. ṣûja<BR>= सव्या, v. gr. comp. 255.f. 258.; lat. scaevus, adjectâ<BR>gutturali sicut in escit pro esit, unde erit, cf. gr.<BR>ἔσϰον; gr. σϰαιός e σϰαϜιος vel e σϰαιϜος, transposito<BR>ι. Fortasse etiam sinister, sinistimus - cf. dexter,<BR>dextimus, gr. comp. 293. - et gr. ἀϱιστεϱός huc pertinent,<BR>ita ut sinis- ortum sit e sivis- et ἀϱιστεϱός e<BR>σαϜιστεϱός, cum semivocales vel liquidae facile inter se<BR>mutentur, v. gr. comp. 20.) (*)<BR>(*) De cognatis formis in linguis Malayicis v. librum<BR>meum Über die Verwandtschaft der malayisch-polynesischen<BR>Sprachen mit den indisch-europäischen p. 86. et 148.<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=371-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=8379" target="_blank">Correction</a>

