सु
3. सु 5. P. A. ut videtur, primitive effundere, libare, in universum,<BR>inde effundere, exprimere succum, exprimere<BR>succum plantae, praesertim asclepiadis acidae. MAH. 1.4695.:<BR>सुषावच बहून् सोमान्; RIGV. 109.4.: सोमम्…सुनोति;<BR>28.6.: इन्द्राय पतवे सुनु सोमम् उलूखल<BR>«Indrae ad bibendum para libamen (asclepiadem<BR>acidam effunde)». Mortarium. 28.8.: मधुमत् सुतम् (*)<BR>«dulce libamen parate (dulce libate)»; 84.1.: {#asAvi<BR>soma indra te#}. (Cf. स्रु, स्नु; fortasse gr. ὕω, nisi hoc<BR>pertinet ad उन्द्, q. v.)<BR>c. अभि id. R. Schl. I.13.5.: अभिषुत्य «succo asclepiadis<BR>acidae extrito» (vid. annot. ad interpret.). Succum<BR>exprimere in universum. MAN. 5.10.: {#yAnicE 'vA 'BizUyante<BR>puzpamUlaPalEH SuBEH#}.<BR>2) aspergere. BHATT. 9.90.:<BR>अभिषोष्यन् रक्तै रक्षांसि.<BR>(*) Imperat. du. praet. multf. (v. gramm. min. ed. 2. 374^b).)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=377-a&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=8491" target="_blank">Correction</a>

सु
4. सु Praef. adj. et adv.<BR>1) bonus, e. c. सुचित्त BAH. bonam<BR>mentem habens. IN. 5.4., सुपराक्रम BAH. bonam fortitudinem<BR>habens. H. 4.14., सुपुत्र bonum filium habens, filio<BR>fortunatus. IN. 5.55.<BR>2) pulcher, e. c. सुमध्यम BAH. pulchrum<BR>medium corpus habens. H. 3.7.<BR>3) valde, e. c.<BR>सुमहत् permagnus. BR. 1.10.<BR>4) facile. SU. 4.24.: सुदृष्ट.<BR>(Hib. so «in compound words signifies goodness,<BR>fitness, aptness or easy», e. c. soailce «a good fashion,<BR>good manners». Primitiva forma su servata est in sucridh<BR>«easy» = सुकृत; fortasse subha «pleasure, delight,<BR>compleat enjoyment» cohaeret cum भाज्, भाग<BR>felicitas praef. सु. Cambro-brit. hu, hy, he, armor. he,<BR>vid. Pictet p. 93. 94.; gr. εὐ.)<BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?cp=377-b&d=BOP" target="_blank">PDF</a><BR><a href="https://yaahi.github.io/?d=bop&e=8492" target="_blank">Correction</a>

